BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:985100
DTSTAMP:20260314T210015Z
DTSTART:20260408T170000Z
DTEND:20260408T195000Z
SUMMARY:Arthur Miller's Death of a Salesman
LOCATION:Winter Garden Theatre, 1634 Broadway, New York NY 10019
DESCRIPTION:<p>Three-time Tony Award winner Nathan Lane, two-time Tony
  Award winner Laurie Metcalf, and Christopher Abbott will return to
  Broadway in Arthur Miller&rsquo;s towering American drama <em>Death of a
  Salesman</em>, with Ben Ahlers, directed by Tony Award winner Joe
  Mantello. <br /><br />Famously described by critic Kenneth Tynan (<em>The
  Observer</em>) as &ldquo;The greatest American play,&rdquo; Arthur
  Miller&rsquo;s <em>Death of a Salesman</em> has been an essential part of
  our national consciousness since its Broadway debut in 1949, and
  throughout every subsequent era. The original production, directed by Elia
  Kazan and starring Lee J. Cobb, won the Pulitzer Prize for Drama, the Tony
  Award&reg; for Best Play, and the New York Drama Critics&rsquo; Circle
  Award.</p>
END:VEVENT
